{"questionId":"25403","questionHtml":"<p>Deduce from part (d)(i) that the complex roots of the equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>z</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>z</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;can be expressed as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>±</mo><mtext>i</mtext><msqrt><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>a</mi></mfenced></msqrt></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>a</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>⇒</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>a</mi></mfenced></msqrt></math>&nbsp;(since&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em><br><br><br><strong>Note:</strong> Accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>±</mo><msqrt><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>a</mi></mfenced></msqrt></math>.</p>\n<p><br><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>±</mo><mi>b</mi><mtext>i=</mtext></mrow></mfenced><mi>a</mi><mo>±</mo><mtext>i</mtext><msqrt><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>a</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>hence the complex roots can be expressed as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>±</mo><mtext>i</mtext><msqrt><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>a</mi></mfenced></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"25403","referenceCode":"22M.3.AHL.TZ1.2e","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Deduce from part (d)(i) that the complex roots of the equation z-rz2-2az+a2+b2=0 can be expressed as a±ig'a.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.7—Solutions of quadratic equations and inequalities, discriminant and nature of roots","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.12—Complex numbers – Cartesian form and Argand diag"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}